## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="321a7-104">Una aplicación hospedados los proveedores desacoplados.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="321a7-104">Decoupled providers are hosted by an application.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="321a7-105">Dos métodos que pueden utilizarse por la aplicación para que estén disponibles las instancias de clases WMI: publicar o revocar o el método de devolución de llamada.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="321a7-105">Two methods can be used by the application to make instances of WMI classes available: publish/revoke or the callback method.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="321a7-106">El método de devolución de llamada usa el <xref:System.Management.Instrumentation.InstrumentationManager.RegisterType%2A> y <xref:System.Management.Instrumentation.InstrumentationManager.UnregisterType%2A> métodos.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="321a7-106">The callback method uses the <xref:System.Management.Instrumentation.InstrumentationManager.RegisterType%2A> and <xref:System.Management.Instrumentation.InstrumentationManager.UnregisterType%2A> methods.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="321a7-107">En el modelo de publicación y revocación, la infraestructura de WMI proporciona el comportamiento predeterminado para muchos de los métodos que hay que escribir manualmente en el método de devolución de llamada.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="321a7-107">In the publish/revoke model, the WMI infrastructure provides default behavior for many of the methods you have to write yourself in the callback method.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="321a7-108">Estos incluyen la enumeración y enlazar métodos.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="321a7-108">These include the enumeration and bind methods.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="321a7-109">En este modelo, la aplicación crea instancias y los publica.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="321a7-109">In this model, the application creates instances and publishes them.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="321a7-110">La aplicación es responsable de garantizar que se respeten las propiedades clave de las clases.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="321a7-110">The application is responsible for ensuring that the key properties of the classes are respected.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="321a7-111">También es responsable de eliminar las instancias de la aplicación.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="321a7-111">The application is also responsible for deleting instances.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="321a7-112">En el modelo de devolución de llamada, la infraestructura de WMI espera que la aplicación tienen métodos que controlan la enumeración, enlace y cualquier otro método necesario para implementar la funcionalidad del proveedor.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="321a7-112">In the callback model, the WMI infrastructure expects the application to have methods that handle enumeration, binding and any other methods required to implement the functionality of the provider.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="321a7-113">Se llama a la aplicación para esta funcionalidad y se produce un error si no existe o no se ha implementado correctamente.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="321a7-113">It calls into the application for this functionality and fails if it does not exist or is not implemented properly.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="321a7-114">La aplicación registra el tipo de sus clases WMI con la infraestructura mediante una llamada a <xref:System.Management.Instrumentation.InstrumentationManager.RegisterType%2A> e indica que ya no desea las clases WMI expuestas mediante una llamada a <xref:System.Management.Instrumentation.InstrumentationManager.UnregisterType%2A>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="321a7-114">The application registers the type of its WMI classes with the infrastructure by calling <xref:System.Management.Instrumentation.InstrumentationManager.RegisterType%2A> and indicates that it no longer wants the WMI classes exposed by calling <xref:System.Management.Instrumentation.InstrumentationManager.UnregisterType%2A>.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="321a7-115">El ejemplo siguiente muestra cómo usar el modelo de publicación/revoke.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="321a7-115">The following example demonstrates how to use the publish/revoke model.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="321a7-116">Se crean dos instancias de la clase de enrutador y se publica.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="321a7-116">Two instances of the router class are created and published.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="321a7-117">Se revoque más adelante.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="321a7-117">They are later revoked.</span></span>  
  
```  
public class Sample_InstanceProvider  
{  
public int Main (string[] args)   
{  
Router r_one = new Router ();  
r_one.Name = "one";  
InstrumentationManager.Publish(r_one);  
Router r_two = new Router ();  
r_two.Name = "two";  
InstrumentationManager.Publish(r_two);  
// ....  
InstrumentationManager.Revoke(r_one);  
InstrumentationManager.Revoke(r_two);  
return 0;  
}  
}  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="321a7-118">En el ejemplo siguiente, el método de devolución de llamada de registro se utiliza para exponer la clase RouterNew.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="321a7-118">In the next example, the callback method of registration is used to expose the RouterNew class.</span></span>  
  
```  
public int MainNew(string[] args)   
{  
    InstrumentationManager.RegisterType(typeof(RouterNew));  
    // ....  
    InstrumentationManager.UnRegisterType(typeof(RouterNew));  
    return 0;  
}  
```

  
  
## Examples  
  
```  
static int Main(string[] args)  
{  
   InstrumentationManager.RegisterType(typeof(MySampleProvider));  
   return 0;  
}  
```
